Privacy Policy
Last updated: Nov 2024
Introduction
Welcome to MonMate. MonMate is an application designed to connect to a MongoDB server. This privacy policy explains how we handle your information when you use our app.
Data Collection and Usage
MonMate does not collect or transfer user data to any server. Your connection to the MongoDB server is managed locally within the app and no personal data is transmitted externally.
Third-Party Services
MonMate integrates third-party services to enhance user experience and app performance:
AdMob:
We use Google AdMob for advertising purposes. AdMob may collect and use data as described in its privacy policy. You can review the AdMob privacy policy
here
.
Crashlytics:
We use Crashlytics for crash reporting and analytics to help improve the app. Crashlytics collects crash data and usage information as described in its privacy policy. You can review the Crashlytics privacy policy
here
.
Open-Source Software
MonMate utilizes open-source software, including:
mongo-dart:
A Dart driver for MongoDB. You can review the mongo-dart project
here
.
MonMate itself is open-source software licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0). You are free to use, modify, and distribute MonMate in accordance with the terms of this license. You can view the source code and contribute to the project on our
GitHub repository
.
Security
We are committed to ensuring the security of your data. While no system is completely secure, we take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: monmate@pahlavan.co.uk